In [[mathematics|mathematical]] [[invariant theory]], an '''evectant''' is a contravariant constructed from an invariant by acting on it with a [[differential operator]] called an  '''evector'''. Evectants and evectors were introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Sylvester|year=1854|loc=p.95}}.

